snippet.textDisplay:
I haven't commented on any of the music since I am not an expert, but this art form truly deserves a dustbin! No rhyme, no theme, no rhythm, just random urdu words mingled together and romanticised using good visuals, anuv jain's facial expressions! Literally Sad to see people being emotional on this CRAP when their country has produced singers like arijit, sonu nigham, shaan and songs like chand sifarish, tum hi ho and many many more! 
Dont call him a singer please! He is not! Just someone who acts to be the most broken one but has nothing to do with emotions or words! Zero impact of his songs.. 
Just a hint so that you can also catch that he isnt a singer.. He always does hayeee, bhaghwaaannnnnnnn, the words which should be spoken normally he just prolongs them unnecessarily!
